          }
        ],
        "author": {
          "name": "Ryan Haasken",
          "email": "haasken@cray.com",
          "date": "2014-03-05 15:23:07.000000000",
          "tz": -360
        },
        "committer": {
          "name": "Oleg Drokin",
          "email": "oleg.drokin@intel.com",
          "date": "2014-04-21 03:41:29.000000000",
          "tz": 0
        },
        "subject": "LU-4711 libcfs: Always clamp cdls_delay between min and max",
        "message": "LU-4711 libcfs: Always clamp cdls_delay between min and max\n\nIn libcfs_debug_vmsg2, cdls_delay is only clamped between the minimum\nand the maximum when it is increased by multiplying by the backoff\nfactor.  It is not clamped when it is decreased by dividing by the\nbackoff factor.  This allows it to achieve values less than the\nminimum, which allows a console message to be printed that should have\nbeen skipped.  This patch moves the clamping outside of the else\nstatement, ensuring that cdls_delay is always between the min and the\nmax after the first time through libcfs_debug_vmsg2.\n\nSigned-off-by: Ryan Haasken <haasken@cray.com>\nChange-Id: I5e587292b73b4c61ef306908fa10d324da5ce069\nReviewed-on: http://review.whamcloud.com/9503\nTested-by: Jenkins\nTested-by: Maloo <hpdd-maloo@intel.com>\nReviewed-by: Chris Horn <hornc@cray.com>\nReviewed-by: Ann Koehler <amk@cray.com>\nReviewed-by: Andreas Dilger <andreas.dilger@intel.com>\n"
      },
      "branch": "refs/heads/master"
    }
  },
